To generate the Terraform configuration for an AWS CodeBuild project with the specified requirements, we'll need to define several resources and configurations.

1. **IAM Role**: The AWS CodeBuild project requires an IAM role that grants permission to AWS CodeBuild services.

2. **GitHub Source Configuration**: Configure the source repository as GitHub, including the URL and access token for accessing the repository.

3. **Build Artifacts**: Specify where the artifacts are stored and how to handle them (e.g., discard them or store as S3 outputs).

4. **Cache Settings**: Configure the build environment to use a cache to speed up builds by reducing download and reuse times for dependencies.

Here's the Terraform configuration in HCL:

```hcl
provider "aws" {
  region = "us-east-1"
}

resource "aws_iam_role" "codebuild_role" {
  name = "CodeBuildRole"

  assume_role_policy {
    version = "2012-10-17" 
    statement = {
      actions = ["sts:AssumeRole"]
      principals {
        type        = "Service"
        identifiers = ["codebuild.amazonaws.com"]
      }
      effect       = "Allow"
      sid          = ""
    }
}

resource "aws_iam_role_policy" "codebuild_policy" {
  role = aws_iam_role.codebuild_role.id

  policy = jsonencode({
    Version = "2012-10-17"
    Statement = [
      {
        Effect = "Allow"
        Action = [
          "logs:CreateLogGroup",
          "logs:CreateLogStream",
          "logs:PutLogEvents"
        ]
        Resource = "arn:aws:logs:*:*:*"
      },
    ]
})

resource "aws_codebuild_project" "sample_codebuild_project" {
  name         = "sample-codebuild-project"
  description  = "A sample AWS CodeBuild project from Terraform"
  build_spec   = "BuildSpec"

  service_role = aws_iam_role.codebuild_role. * arn

  source_type    = "GITHUB"
  git_clone_depth = 1
  insecure_ssl    = true

  artifacts = {
    type = "NO_ARTIFACTS"
  }

  environment {
    compute_type      = "BUILD_GENERAL1_SMALL"
    image              = "aws/codebuild/standard:1.0"
    type       = "LINUX"
    image_pull_credentials_type = "CODEBUILD"
    environment_variable {
      name  = "SECRET"
      value = "mysecret"
      type  = "PLAINTEXT"
    }
  }

  cache {
    mode = "S3"
    location = "arn:aws:s3:::mybucket/cache"
    encryption_disabled = false
    encrypt_env_vars = true
  }
}

resource "aws_codebuildsin_source_type" "source" {
  type = "GITHUB"
  location = "https://github.com/myorganization/myrepository.git"
  auth {
    type = "OAUTH"
    resource = "arn:aws:iam::123456789012:role/role-for-github"
  }
}
```

Please replace "mybucket", "mysecret", "myorganization", and "myrepository" with actual values for your specific project. You'll also need to set up the variable resource (e.g., OAUTH token) within the GitHub source configuration as needed.

This Terraform configuration assumes you have the appropriate AWS CodeBuild project setup using the specified IAM permissions and S3 location/cache for the storage, while configuring the environment and artifacts according to your requirements.

