response:
To configure AWS EKS pod identity using Terraform, we'll follow these steps:

1. **Define an IAM Policy Document**: This document will allow EKS pods to assume a specific IAM role.

2. **Create an IAM Role**: Using the policy document, establish an IAM role that EKS pods can assume.

3. **Attach S3 Read-Only Access Policy**: Assign this policy to the created IAM role to provide S3 read-only access.

4. **Associate the IAM Role with the EKS Pod Identity**: Use the EKS pod identity feature to associate the IAM role with the EKS cluster and namespace.

Below is the complete Terraform configuration in HCL format:

```hcl
variable "cluster_name" {
  description = "The name of the EKS cluster"
  type        = string
}

variable "namespace" {
  description = "The Kubernetes namespace to associate the role with"
  type = string
}

variable "service_account" {
  description = "The name of the Kubernetes service account to associate"
  type = string
}

data "aws_iam_policy" "s3_read_only" {
  name = "arn:aws:iam::aws:policy/AmazonS3ReadOnlyAccess"
}

resource "aws_iam_policy_document" "example_policy" {
  statement {
    effect    = "Allow"
    actions   = ["sts:AssumeRole"]
    resources = ["*"]
  }
}

resource "aws_iam_role" "example_role" {
  name               = "example"
  assume_role_policy  = aws_iam_policy_document.example_policy.json
}

resource "aws_iam_role_policy_attachment" "example_role_s3_attachment" {
  role       = aws_iam_role.example_role.name
  policy_arn  = data.aws_iam_policy.s3_read_only.arn
}

resource "aws_iam_role_policy" "example_role_policy" {
  role = aws_iam_role.example_role.name
  policy = aws_iam_policy.example_policy_document.id
}

resource "aws_eks_pod_identity_association" "example_association" {
  cluster_name = var.cluster_name
  namespace   = var.namespace
  service_account = var.service_account
  iam_role   = aws_iam_role.example_role.name
}
```

### Make Sure to Set Your Variables:

- `cluster_name`: The name of your EKS cluster, e.g., "example".
- `namespace`: The namespace within your Kubernetes cluster to associate the role with.
- `service_account`: The name of the Kubernetes service account to associate with the IAM role.
- Ensure the role's ARNs (e.g., S3 read-only policy) are correctly configured in your account as appropriate permissions.

This configuration effectively sets up an IAM role for EKS pods, attaches necessary permissions for S3 read-only access, and associates the role with the specified EKS cluster and namespace through Terraform.

