- Replace `unique-bucket-name-for-pdf` with a unique name for your S3 bucket. S3 bucket names need to be globally unique.
- The region is set to `us-east-1`, but you can change it according to your requirements. 
- The `source` attribute of `aws_s3_bucket_object` points to the local file you want to upload. Adjust the path to `assets/test.pdf` if it resides elsewhere on your system.
- The `etag` attribute ensures that if the file doesn't change, Terraform will not re-upload it, avoiding unnecessary operations.

